# Vercel Web Analytics Implementation

Successfully implemented Vercel Web Analytics for the Next.js IOT-HUB project.

## Changes Made

### 1. Installed Package
- Added `@vercel/analytics` package to dependencies
- Used npm to install the package as the project uses package-lock.json

### 2. Modified Files

**src/app/layout.tsx**
- Added import statement: `import { Analytics } from "@vercel/analytics/next"`
- Added `<Analytics />` component inside the `<body>` tag, after the SessionProviderComp closing tag
- The component is properly placed to track all page views across the application

**package.json**
- Added `@vercel/analytics` to dependencies

**package-lock.json**
- Updated with @vercel/analytics and its dependencies

## Implementation Details

This is an App Router Next.js project (using `src/app` directory structure), so the Analytics component was added to the root layout file (`src/app/layout.tsx`).

The `<Analytics />` component is placed:
- Inside the `<body>` tag for proper script injection
- After all other provider components to ensure proper initialization
- At the root level to track all routes in the application

